# Cursor Rules — This Repository

**Scope:** These rules apply to **this workspace** (the folder that contains `.cursor/rules/`). They are not global to your machine. To reuse the same workflow in another repo, copy `.cursor/` (or this rule + skills) into that project, or add equivalent instructions under **Cursor → Settings → Rules → User rules** for all projects.

## Important: Read Project Context First

At the start of **every** new conversation, you MUST read these in order:

1. **`.cursor/skills/task-management-workflow/SKILL.md`** — Task proposals, to-do lists, task summaries, progress updates, and naming conventions. **Read this file in full every time** (not only when the user mentions tasks).
2. **`IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md`** — Single source of truth for high-level phases and status
3. **`structure/latest.md`** — Current project structure and file organization
4. **`progress/latest.md`** — Active tasks and completion status
5. **`task_summary/YYYYMM/YYYYMMDD/[most_recent].md`** — Most recent task summary (when continuing work)

**`README.md`** (repo root) — Short project overview and pointers; optional if this rule is already loaded.

These files contain essential information about the project setup, workflow, and coding standards that should be followed throughout all conversations.

---

## Overview

This project uses a structured workflow to track tasks and proposals systematically. For task-specific procedures, follow **task-management-workflow** (see step 1 above). Other guidance lives in `.cursor/skills/`.

## Project Execution Policy

- `IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md` is the authoritative high-level phase plan.
- Any new phase/subphase or phase status change must be updated in `IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md` first, then synchronized to task/progress docs.
- Agent may create/modify/download files without per-file confirmation when file size is **<= 200 MB**.
- For files expected to be **> 200 MB**, agent must inform the user before proceeding.
- After each completed subtask, update `conversation_cursor`, `to-do`, `task_summary`, `structure/latest.md`, and `progress/latest.md`.

## Folder Organization

```
conversation_cursor/     [TASK PROPOSALS]
├── YYYYMM/
│   └── YYYYMMDD/
│       └── task_name.md

to-do/                   [TASK CHECKLISTS]
├── YYYYMM/
│   └── YYYYMMDD/
│       └── task_name.md

task_summary/            [TASK SUMMARIES]
├── YYYYMM/
│   └── YYYYMMDD/
│       └── task_name.md

progress/                [PROGRESS TRACKING]
└── latest.md            → Active & completed tasks

structure/               [PROJECT DOCUMENTATION]
└── latest.md            → Project structure & file descriptions

IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md   [SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH]
                        → High-level project phases and status
```

## Cursor Skills

Skills are in `.cursor/skills/`. **task-management-workflow** is mandatory reading each conversation (see above). Others are used when relevant:

- **task-management-workflow** — Task file management, updates, completion (always read at conversation start)
- **file-creation-rules** — File creation permissions and naming conventions
- **r-package-development** — R environment, package loading, script execution
- **hpc4-execution** — HPC4 conda environment, AWS config, SLURM jobs
- **aws-s3-data-management** — S3 credentials, load/write operations
- **coding-style** — R and C++ code formatting standards
- **git-rules** — Git workflow and commit message format

See `.cursor/skills/` for the full list.

